name: Bright & Airy- A/C, Full Kitchen, W/D
neighborhood_overview:
Princeville is an amazingly convenient and beautiful community on the North Shore. Here's why you'll love it:

From the condo location it is easy to walk to the beach or the grocery store and the views in either direction are spectacular, with ocean one direction and mountains and waterfalls the other! In fact there is a network of fantastic walking and running trails all over Princeville, making it likely the safest and easiest of locations of the island to walk or take a run. Another bonus is that many of the nearby golf courses are open for pedestrian exploration after 5pm, which is beyond excellent for sunset strolls.

The coastline below Princeville provides some of the most pristine, clear water on the North Shore due to the lack of rivers and fresh water runoff. Because of this, Princeville has some amazing exploring to enjoy below its bluffs (surf conditions permitting!!). The clear water provides some of the very best turtle viewing, snorkeling, pristine co
host_about:
Aloha! I am Lani and I am passionate about sharing and passing on the love I have for my island Home of Kauai to those who visit this special place.

I’ve lived on Kauai for much of my life. I was born near Tunnels Beach and have always considered the North Shore of Kauai “home”. However, adventures beyond the islands, eventually brought me to the mainland and abroad.  I went to school in Santa Cruz California and even got interested in colder climates for a while. Between travels abroad, I worked as an entrepreneur and in various outdoor industries for the better part of a decade, living in amazingly scenic, rural towns. One of my favorite of those towns was Jackson Hole Wyoming, where I lived for several years before moving back to Kauai. It took searching the world to ultimately realize, there’s no place like home.  

I truly enjoy passing on the love and reverence I have of my island home to my guests. I offer my local knowledge and recommendations in addition to providing exceptional quality accommodation and service. I want to ensure that my guests have as much fun and as little worries as possible on their visits to Kauai!

I love offering conscientious  travelers an amazing home while they explore the Garden Island, and both my condos are thoughtfully equipped, well located and always kept clean and attended to with lots of love.

I am are honored to have received such great reviews, and maintained a consistent Airbnb SuperHost rating that I have held strong for several years.

I am grateful for my guests, as they give to me just as much as I give them.

Happiest of travels and lots of Aloha to you!

Lani

neighborhood_overview:
Kula, in upcountry Maui, is a peaceful, "local", and gorgeous area, with a combination of ranch land, open space, and small neighborhoods. The closest neighbors to Kula Jewel are a work-at-home jeweler, a work-at-home photographer, a man who builds beautiful garden fountains, an accupuncturist with a home office, a massage/Reiki therapist with a home studio, and your host, a voice/‘ukulele teacher/professional musician. We all love the peaceful quality of our neighborhood, and hope you will want to help us preserve that quality. The Kula Lodge has "fine dining", but we ALWAYS recommend the Kula Bistro instead. The Bistro has exceptional food, large portions and is more reasonably priced than the Lodge. Upon check-in, Pamela will give you directions to all the local eateries, and if your stay crosses over a Saturday, donʻt miss the Kula Farmerʻs Market - one of the best food experiences anywhere on Maui!
Kula Jewel is the perfect jumping off point for Haleakalā sunrise, sunset or
host_about:
Iʻm a professional musician and voice & ‘ukulele teacher. I live on Maui because I love the beauty, the quiet, the ocean and all its creatures. Iʻm blessed with good health, and great friends and a truly beautiful home.

I've been deeply involved with Hawaiian culture for the last 25+ years, studying the language, music, crafts and hula.
I also teach ‘ukulele, and several of my guests have taken lessons with me while staying at Kula Treat. I recently was accepted to the AirBnB Experiences program as the ‘ukulele teacher for Maui!  (Iʻm very honored by this, and excited to share my love of the ‘ukulele with visitors from all over the world).

 As an AirBnB host, I love hosting travelers because I think my home, and the area where I live, give visitors a true sense of what itʻs like to live on Maui - away from the touristy areas. My style of hosting is to show my guests everything they'll need, (how to use the tv or hot tub, for instance, where coffee and teas are stored, etc.), and then leave them to their privacy. At the same time, I'm generally available for questions or anything my guests might need for their comfort, if it's not already presented.

Come experience Maui with Kula Jewel, or Kula Treat (my two listings) as your home base. And sign up for an ‘ukulele lesson if thereʻs time in your vacation schedule.
E komo mai! (Welcome!)

ps Iʻm very pleased to announce that both my listings are fully permitted by Maui County, and any reservation you make with me will be legal and secure. Woo hoo!!

name: 1 Bedroom Standard w/Kitchen-Kamaole Sands #8302
host_about:
Vacationing in Maui doesn’t get better than Kamaole Sands, a condo resort built on 15 acres of gardens, waterfalls, and ponds. Live like you’ve always wanted to in an individually furnished condominium suite directly across from Kihei’s popular Kamaole Beach Park III. Defined by its laid-back vibe and tropical beauty, South Maui is a true Hawaiian paradise.

Our dreamy Kihei location near Wailea Resort and Makena Resort puts you in the midst of golf, spas and ocean recreation.

- Learn to surf at Kamaole Beach Park III
- Tee off at Maui Nui or Wailea golf clubs
- Stay on trend at The Shops at Wailea
- Snorkel amid the pristine waters of La Perouse Bay
- Indulge in spa treatments at Wailea Resort
- Sample craft brews at Maui Brewing Company

The best plan for your day is often no plan at all. Maybe you’ll start your morning with a swim in the Pacific or in our pool. You might mingle amid traveling kindred spirits at your resort’s Wednesday Mai Tai Party, and then grill a fresh catch with your new friends at the property’s public barbecue area. Or step out for a sunset dinner at one of Kihei’s fantastic cafes or bistros. Need to stay connected? We offer complimentary WiFi in the lobby, pool area, and all rooms.

Since 1993, Castle Resorts & Hotels has specialized in innovative hotel and resort management. We manage properties throughout the Hawaiian Islands, including Kauai, Oahu, Maui, Molokai, and Hawaii Island, as well as Auckland, New Zealand. Accommodations range from full-service hotels to resort condominiums and combines value, convenience, and authentic experiences.

Take a boat cruise on a whale-watching excursion, or survey the diverse landscape on a scenic hike. For a little island flavor, dine at any of the fine local restaurants. Experience Hawaii where endless activities, spectacular shows and breathtaking sunsets await you in Maui.

name: Big Island Sanctuary
neighborhood_overview:
Our neighborhood was made famous during the 2018 eruption of the Kilauea volcano. Please be respectful of the lava - it is beautiful to look at, but do not touch it or walk on it. Lava covered private properties and homes in the neighborhood, and it is illegal to walk on the lava in the neighborhood. Also, it is unsafe to walk on the lava. Please enjoy its beauty without touching it, as well as all of the tropical Hawaiian beauty around you!

Additionally, the iconic Puna Coast is within a 15 minute drive (Highway 137 tracks the coastline). Volcano National Park is less than an hour away, and Hilo is 30 min away.
host_about:
Hi Airbnb,

Some of our favorite places to travel:  Greece, London, the Big Island of Hawaii, and the Cinque Terre (Italy).  But any place that opens our eyes to new things is great.  

We share our time between San Francisco and the Big Island. Jon works in solar energy and Fahmida in neuropsychology. 

We are both from the Midwest, primarily reside in San Francisco and were married on the Big Island. We purchased our first home on the Big Island because it is a special place for us. 

As hosts we want share the aloha spirit and the sanctuary of our peaceful retreat with you. 

Hope to be traveling in your neck of the woods soon or sharing our part of the woods with you. 

Fahmida & Jon

Located on the South Kohala coast of the island of Hawaii, the Waikoloa area is rich in ancient Hawaiian history and culture that stand side-by-side with modern full-service resorts. The rugged and undeveloped coastline is lined with scenic valleys, lava fields, and golf courses. Step back in time, by strolling the ancient pathways that lead to petroglyph fields and traditional fishponds, head to the beach to experience the crystal-clear waters of Hapuna Beach State Park or the jet-black shores of Punaluu Beach, or shop and dine at the numerous shops and restaurants in the resort area.

Kalapaki, is the most centrally located resort destination, making the drive to explore both the West Side and the North Shore somewhat equal, although opposite directions. This is important to keep in mind if you are planning to fully explore the entire island, as it will spare a rather lengthy drive should you stay on either the West Side or the North Shore, and therefore need to drive from one side back to the other in one day.

neighborhood_overview:
Welcome to your dream getaway along the famous "Red Road". In paradise our secluded jungle location offers an unforgettable experience, just 2 miles from the renowned black sand beach (Kehena).

Immerse yourself in the vibrant local culture by exploring the Kaimu Farmer's market on Saturday mornings, a mere 5 miles away. Indulge in the eclectic offerings of artisan vendors, delectable prepared food, and fresh produce at the lively Maku'u market on Sunday mornings, conveniently located just 10 miles from your haven. Don't forget a visit to Uncle Robert's. A local gathering place for food music and traditional Awa (kava) since 1962. Try to get there Wednesday evenings for live music.

For a fascinating journey into nature's artistry, take a scenic 30-minute drive to the Lava Tree State Monument. Marvel at the captivating lava molds left behind by the historic 1790 flow—a testament to the raw power of the island's volcanic history. Don't forget to carve out time for

Situated on the cliffside overlooking the Pacific, this family-friendly vacation ownership resort is near Anini Beach and a short drive from picturesque Hanalei Bay. Explore The Wai`oli Mission and splendid 1,000-acre Limahuli Garden. Unwind and refuel after your adventures at Princeville Bistro or Nanea Bar & Grill restaurant. After you experience the North Shore activities, energize at the 24-hour WestinWORKOUT® Fitness Studio or swim in one of the sparkling outdoor pools overlooking the ocean at Princeville oceanfront resort. Embrace pure tranquility with a soothing massage in an open-air cabana. Renew your body and soul at The Westin Princeville Ocean Resort Villas.

Please note that accessing the beach from the resort involves navigating through a cliffside terrain.

NEARBY BEACHES:

- Anini Beach: Approximately 10 minutes
- Hideaways Beach: Approximately 5 minutes

Vacation Home Management

Vacasa unlocks the possibilities of how we enjoy vacation homes. We take care of managing our homeowners’ vacation houses so they can have peace of mind (and their home when they want to). And our guests book vacations confidently knowing they’re going to find exactly what they’re looking for without any surprises.

Our passion and focus remain true: to empower our homeowners, guests, and employees to invest in vacation.

neighborhood_overview: The property is part of Country Club Villas which is a beautiful and tranquil community. It is a safe neighborhood with security cameras in the parking lot and their is a sidewalk path which leads you to the Keauhou Shopping Plaza which has a grocery store, restaurants, shopping, a pharmacy, a movie theater, and bike rentals.

name: Beachfront Condo | 30 Day Min | Pool + A/C
neighborhood_overview:
Enjoy oceanfront access right on the beach! The nearby reef protects the area, making it ideal for snorkeling in calm waters, while larger wave beaches are just a short distance away. You'll find a variety of food options, including shrimp, Thai, burger, and Vietnamese food trucks, as well as a Hawaiian ice stand and convenience store just a half-block away.


Less than 5 miles from the Polynesian Cultural Center, Hawaii’s top paid attraction, featuring world-class entertainment, shows, and luaus. Two grocery stores and a Longs drugstore are nearby for your convenience. Laie Beach Park, known for its excellent body surfing, is only five minutes away, and Turtle Bay Resort offers golf and dining just a short drive from the condo.

Hi, my husband and I grew up and live in Los Angeles, CA. We have 1 son with autism. Our goal was always to introduce our son to new places and things to try and help him grow leaps and bounds. What we found was traveling was the most effective. So since then, we have immersed him into many different environments on our journey of growing as a whole family. We love helping others grow and enhance their love for life through travel. Please before booking confirm with us the dates you are looking to travel as the Airbnb calendar sometimes has issues updating itself.

Our Warmest Wishes, Happy Travels!
